{"id":1271025834,"question_id":345,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"3 weeks, 6 days","timestamp":1716956587,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"2 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1271025834/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Reverse Vowels of a String","memory":"44.8 MB","code":"class Solution {        \n    public boolean isVowel(char c)\n    {\n        if(c=='a' || c=='A' || c=='e' || c=='E' || c=='i' || c=='I' || c=='o' || c=='O' || c=='u' || c=='U')\n        {    \n            return true;\n        }    \n        return false;    \n    }\n    public String reverseVowels(String s) {\n        char[] str = s.toCharArray();\n        int i=0, j = str.length-1;\n        \n        while(i<j){\n            char ci = str[i];\n            char cj = str[j];\n            if(isVowel(ci) && isVowel(cj)){\n                str[i++] = cj;\n                str[j--] = ci;\n            }else{\n                if(!isVowel(ci))\n                    i++;\n                if(!isVowel(cj))\n                    j--;\n            }\n        }\n        \n        return new String(str);\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"reverse-vowels-of-a-string","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
